org.apache.jackrabbit.core.observation
Class EventFilter

java.lang.Object
  org.apache.jackrabbit.core.observation.EventFilter
class EventFilter
extends Object

The EventFilter class implements the filter logic based on the session's access rights and the specified filter rules.

EventFilter

EventFilter(ItemManager itemMgr,
            SessionImpl session,
            long eventTypes,
            Path path,
            boolean isDeep,
            String[] uuids,
            NodeTypeImpl[] nodeTypes,
            boolean noLocal)
Creates a new EventFilter instance.

Parameters:
itemMgr - the ItemManager of the session.
session - the Session that registered the EventListener.
eventTypes - only allow specified EventTypes.
path - only allow Item with path.
isDeep - if true also allow events for Items below absPath.
uuids - only allow events for Nodes with specified UUIDs. If null is passed no restriction regarding UUID is applied.
nodeTypes - only allow events for specified NodeTypes. If null no node type restriction is applied.
noLocal - if true no events are allowed that were created from changes related to the Session that registered the EventListener.
